THE JOB

Reporting to the Sports Medicine Manager,the Senior Sport Physiotherapist will be responsible for the following duties:

To provide physiotherapy treatment and rehabilitation services for scholarship athletes and to provide overseas on-field support;
To act as case Manager to implement and enhance communication with other professionals in the same Center and other Centers to foster the program results;
To act as a team leader to monitor and review the daily operation and productivity of the team;
To provide clinical and professional supervision to the subordinates;
To keep abreast of the up-to-date theory and practice as well as implementing staff training;
To assist in planning and development of the Centers ; and
To perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
THE REQUIREMENTS
A post-graduate degree in physiotherapy or musculoskeletal physiotherapy  or a relevant discipline;
Must be eligible to be registered by the Hong Kong Physiotherapy Board, with a minimum of 6 years’ physiotherapy or sports relevant working experience
Experience in managing sports injury;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
 Excellent command of both spoken and written English and Chinese. Ability to speak Putonghua is a definite advantage; and
 Awareness/ knowledge of Child Protection in sport and equal opportunity issues in the context of Hong Kong are an added advantage.


