DEPARTMENT OF REHABILITATION SCIENCES
Physiotherapist I (Rehabilitation Clinic) (Ref. 22010602-IE)
Duties
The appointee will be required to:
(a)   Provide physiotherapy services to patients attending the Rehabilitation Clinic;
(b)   Provide on-field physiotherapy service;
(c)   Conduct health-related talks and exercise classes;
(d)   Supervise on-site and off-site clinical placements;
(e)   Provide administrative support;
(f)    Assist in the promotion and development of clinic services;
(g)   Participate in classroom teaching and practical/laboratory sessions; and
(h)   Perform any other duties as assigned by the Head of Department or his/her delegates.
Qualifications
Applicants should:
(a)     Have a bachelor’s degree in Physiotherapy or equivalent, preferably with a master’s degree in Sports Physiotherapy / Musculoskeletal Physiotherapy / Neurological Rehabilitation;
(b)     Be registered with the Hong Kong Physiotherapists Board and have a valid practicing certificate;
(c)     Have at least five years of relevant post-qualification working experience in the fields such as sports physiotherapy / musculoskeletal physiotherapy / neurological rehabilitation;
(d)     Have proven clinical experience and skills in the areas of musculoskeletal / neurological rehabilitation;
(e)     Have good interpersonal and communication skills; and
(f)      Be independent and able to work with other disciplines.
Remuneration and Conditions of Service
A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Initial appointment will be on a fixed-term gratuity-bearing contract.  Re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.
Application
Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or email by clicking "Apply now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  Consideration of applications will commence on 20 January 2022 until the position is filled.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.
PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

